            <thetext>Using the latest mobile master, it seems that I cannot manage to have a form inside a carousel. The form fields appear writable, but they cannot get focus.
It works correctly on any desktop browser running the mobile app, but as soon as on ios (7), either on device or simulator, the fields become read-only.

A simple test case :
http://tinyurl.com/nuws5gs

As a quick workaround, commenting the following line in the Carousel constructor restores the expected behaviour :

// carouselScroller.addListener(&quot;touchstart&quot;, qx.bom.Event.preventDefault, this);</thetext>
